item.title: GSWSCO
item.description: GSWSCO is an in-progress project that aims to provide a comprehensive, easy-to-use, and extensible way to manage utility infrastructure networks.

item.title: GeoHub
item.description: UNDP GeoHub is a United Nations Development Programme (UNDP)’s cloud-based ecosystem for geospatial data, serving as a centralized platform where UNDP staff and policymakers can create, share, visualize, and analyze spatial data to support evidence-based development, particularly for achieving the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs).

item.title: GoalSpatial COGServer
item.description: GoalSpatial COGServer is a cloud-based COG server for serving large COGs as tiles. This project is maintained by the GoalSpatial team.
